    <h1 class="display-4">@ViewData["Title"]'s Gaming Stack</h1>
    <p class="text-start">
        Playing video games has always been a great way for me to unwind and
        challenge myself, and two of my favorites are Rainbow Six Siege and 
        Rocket League. Siege is an intense tactical shooter that demands 
        strategy, teamwork, and quick decision-making, making every match a 
        unique and rewarding experience. Whether I’m coordinating with teammates 
        to execute a perfect breach or adapting to unpredictable enemy tactics, 
        the game keeps me engaged with its deep mechanics and strategic depth. 
        On the other hand, Rocket League offers a completely different but 
        equally thrilling challenge—fast-paced, high-flying soccer with 
        rocket-powered cars. The combination of precision, speed, and 
        aerial maneuvers makes every match exciting, and there’s always room 
        to improve my skills and pull off insane plays.
    </p>
    <p class="text-start">
        What I love most about these games is the mix of competition and teamwork.
        Rainbow Six Siege pushes me to think critically under pressure, 
        communicate effectively, and adapt my strategies to outplay opponents. 
        Meanwhile, Rocket League is all about mechanical skill, coordination, 
        and creativity, whether I'm setting up a perfect pass or scoring a clutch 
        goal. Both games provide a sense of progression and mastery that keeps 
        me coming back for more. Beyond just playing, they’ve also helped me 
        connect with friends and engage with a broader gaming community. Whether 
        I’m grinding ranked matches or just having fun, these games continue 
        to be a favorite way to relax and push my limits.
    </p>
